latestPosts.caption:
Donated 18 inches (120 grams) of hair to @wigs.for.kids 

Five years ago, I began a transformative journey to reclaim my hair after battling years of excessive hair loss. It was a promise I made to myself: to nurture my hair naturally, without any chemical treatments, all for a greater purpose. Each inch that grew was a reminder of hope and resilience. Finally, the day came when I could donate 18 inches of my hair to Wigs for Kids. My heart swelled with joy, knowing that my gift could bring happiness and a boost of confidence to a child who needed it. 

May this act of kindness inspire others to share their journeys and remind us all that even the smallest gestures can create a ripple of positive change.

A heartfelt thank you to @sarahbaddass for cutting and styling my hair so beautifully. You truly made today unforgettable! 🤍✨

Starting the year with a fresh cut and thrilled to bring you all on my hair growth journey! 

#2025 #hair #haircut #trend #trendingreels #donate #beauty #shorthair #hairgoals

latestPosts.caption:
March dump: HEALING•NOURISHMENT•FAITH

This month began just like any other, but a week later, I found myself spiraling into chronic pain. It presented a choice: to view it as an excuse or as an opportunity for growth. I had the chance to confront a battle I had been quietly enduring—either accept it as my norm or dig deeper to uncover the root of the issue, placing my trust in God throughout the journey 🤍 So long March- you made me stronger 🦾

Thankful for my circle. 
Couldn’t have done it without 🥲🫂💐

1 urgent care visit 
1 x-rays 🩻 
1 MRI 🦾
1 labs 🧪 
3 doc visits 🩺
Lots of pain meds, muscle relaxers and sleepless nights
